<title>UK: SIG to sell SIGAP unit to management.</title>
<headline>SIG to sell SIGAP unit to management.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-03-03</dateline>
<text>
<p>British insulation products manufacturer SIG Plc said on Monday it had conditionally agreed to sell its hardware and security division SIGAP to its management for 65 million stg.</p>
<p>SIG said the management buy-out was being led by David Kent, managing director of SIGAP, and a group of senior managers supported by NatWest Ventures. A new company, Moldstate Ltd, would be formed to operate the venture.</p>
<p>--London Newsroom +44 171 542 4017</p>
